  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to know which devices we want to support (i.e. have acceptable perf on) in order to do relevant profiling, testing and fixing.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature/Decision\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Make a list of supported devices on Android and iOS respectively. Alternatively set a minimum/reference device version for each platform that we can use for benchmarking.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nA clear list or pair of devices we want to support for each platform.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNo such thing.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nSome considerations:\r\n\r\n- QA and devs should have access to these\r\n- It's OK to be a bit bleeding edge because users will catch up\r\n- But perhaps not \"iPhone X only\" bleeding edge\r\n- Android market share is very fractured, there's a long tail and seems difficult to get 80/20 (80% market share out of few devices), see e.g. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1HAK3KstFqbVThQxWzLGoJXcq-U3x2NojZyt6_RIg4Ak/edit#gid=1051777509\r\n\r\nPremium for quick decision on this front; easy to iterate. Example: iPhone7+ and Samsung Galaxy S7+ (not based on anything, just two reasonably new models)",
